<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,334,267,293]" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1398,317,383]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Thin encrusting sponge, dark blue colored; it covers colonies of the octocoral 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1159,318,344]" class="Anthozoa" family="Clavulariidae" genus="Carijoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1159,318,344]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Carijoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (Class 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1834" box="[1277,1394,317,343]" class="Anthozoa" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="class">Anthozoa</taxonomicName>
, Phylum Cnidaria) (
<figureCitation box="[414,524,356,383]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,953,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1398,953,1913]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 26. Terpios granulosus Bergquist, 1967. A. Sponge (PO96) encrusting the octocoral Carijoa sp. B. Tylostyles organized in brushes (SEM). C. Tylostyle and magnification of heads, different in shape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3978563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3978563/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). Whitish in ethanol, bluish in formalin. The surface is microhispid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1399,425,491]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
SKELETON. It is formed by brushes of spicules which, projecting also over the surface, cause the microhispid surface (
<figureCitation box="[437,545,464,491]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,953,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1398,953,1913]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 26. Terpios granulosus Bergquist, 1967. A. Sponge (PO96) encrusting the octocoral Carijoa sp. B. Tylostyles organized in brushes (SEM). C. Tylostyle and magnification of heads, different in shape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3978563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3978563/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 26B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1399,533,599]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
SPICULES. Tylostyles with heads variable in shape, from mushroom-shape to plurilobate (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1334,533,560]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,953,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[189,1398,953,1913]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 26. Terpios granulosus Bergquist, 1967. A. Sponge (PO96) encrusting the octocoral Carijoa sp. B. Tylostyles organized in brushes (SEM). C. Tylostyle and magnification of heads, different in shape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3978563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3978563/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 26C</figureCitation>
). The size is 77.5–(255, 81.7)– 
<quantity box="[478,570,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="330.0">330 µm</quantity>
×1.25–(4.1, 0.9)– 
<quantity box="[784,847,572,599]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,303,642,668]" box="[189,303,642,668]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,642,668]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,642,668]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[189,1399,692,835]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
The peculiar shape of the heads, the general morphology and the skeletal structure are typical characters of species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864" authorityName="Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti" authorityYear="1864" box="[470,957,731,757]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Terpios" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[470,557,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Terpios</emphasis>
Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen fits the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bergquist, 1967)" baseAuthorityName="Bergquist" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[189,627,770,797]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Terpios" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="granulosus">
<emphasis box="[189,413,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Terpios granulosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist" box="[429,618,770,797]" firstAuthor="Bergquist" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="159 - 174" refId="ref19727" refString="Bergquist P. R. 1967. Additions to the sponge fauna of the Hawaiian Islands. Micronesica 3 (2): 159 - 174." type="journal article" year="1967">Bergquist, 1967</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Hawaii later also recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacelet &amp; Vasseur" box="[1049,1349,770,796]" firstAuthor="Vacelet" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="51 - 126" refId="ref22168" refString="Vacelet J. &amp; Vasseur P. 1971. Eponges des recifs coralliens de Tulear (Madagascar). Tethys, Supplement 1: 51 - 126." type="journal article" year="1971">Vacelet &amp; Vasseur (1971)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnes &amp; Bell" box="[189,442,809,835]" firstAuthor="Barnes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="350 - 359" refId="ref19532" refString="Barnes D. K. A. &amp; Bell J. J. 2002. Coastal sponge communities of the West Indian Ocean: morphological, richness and diversity. African Journal of Ecology 40: 350 - 359. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1365 - 2028.2002.00388. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Barnes &amp; Bell (2002)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[514,591,809,835]" name="Kenya" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[648,792,809,835]" name="Madagascar" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
